cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SD 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper deals with code changes and commits, and proposes a tool to help developers share untangled commits. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper deals with code changes and their relationships to tasks. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possibility as the paper mentions using a novel approach, but it is not the main focus of the paper. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possibility as the paper mentions historical analyses of the project, but again, it is not the main focus. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is a possibility as the paper deals with the concept of "untangling" code changes, but it is not related to sound.
